==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dispositive
<hw>Dis*pos"i*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>dispositif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Disposing; tending to
regulate; decretive.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His <qex>dispositive</qex> wisdom and power.</q>
<rj><qau>Bates.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Belonging to disposition or natural, tendency.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Dispositive</xex> holiness.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dispositively</ent>⟦br⟧
